cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is about fine-grained image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method combines vision and language, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, making it relevant to the subfield of NLP in computer science (cs.CL). The use of deep learning models for representation learning also suggests that it could be relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method on a widely used dataset for fine-grained image classification suggests that it could also be relevant to the subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
